damn yet another super nice and snappy article, lucky me

I'll stuff my thoughts and whatnot under a collapsible seeing as others have done so too.

+Stuff

-thot


The overall feeling I've been left with is that this flips the whole 'gone but not forgotten' idiom on its head. And for that alone I like it.

It's a brief article but for all that it's composed of it has an incredible level of emotion to it as well - definitely a scenario of 'less is more' that has been pulled off exceptionally well.

I will also add that it is, in its own way, quite unnerving too  as Nico put it, it's this sense of futility it evokes in that eventually you will be forgotten (and the more I personally think on it, the more unnerving it gets).

All in all it feels like a very well-rounded, open-and-close case  except unlike an open-and-close case there's no sense of closure, and instead I'm left with a mild feeling of existential despair and a need to go hug the dog. I'mma go do that.




Tl;dr, very much not what I was expecting when I finished reading it, and it did not disappoint.

+1, for making me feel things.








